Trends in Disability-Free Life Expectancy (DFLE) from 1995 to 2017 in the older 
Norwegian population by sex and education: The HUNT Study.

Storeng SH(1)(2), Øverland S(3)(4), Skirbekk V(5)(6)(7)(8), Hopstock LA(9), Sund 
ER(10)(11)(12), Krokstad S(10)(12), Strand BH(2)(8)(13).

Author information:
(1)Department of Public Health and Nursing, Faculty of Medicine and Health 
Sciences, NTNU - Norwegian University of Science and Technology, Norway.
(2)Department of Chronic Diseases and Ageing, Norwegian Institute of Public 
Health, Norway.
(3)Center for Disease Burden, Norwegian Institute of Public Health, Norway.
(4)Department of Psychosocial Science, Faculty of Psychology, University of 
Bergen, Norway.
(5)Centre for Fertility and Health, Norwegian Institute of Public Health, 
Norway.
(6)Columbia Aging Center, Mailman School of Public Health, Columbia University, 
US.
(7)Department of Psychology, University of Oslo, Norway.
(8)Department of Geriatric Medicine, Oslo University Hospital, Norway.
(9)Department of Community Medicine, Faculty of Health Sciences, UiT The Arctic 
University of Norway, Norway.
(10)HUNT Research Centre, Department of Public Health and Nursing, Faculty of 
