PMID: 33913311 [Indexed for MEDLINE]


987. Ugeskr Laeger. 2021 Apr 26;183(17):V10200751.

[Malignant pleural effusion].

[Article in Danish]

Fjællegaard K(1), Petersen JK, Armbruster K, Jensen HK, Skaarup SH, Laursen CB, 
Clementsen PF, Bødtger U.

Author information:
(1)kafj@regionsjaelland.dk.

Malignant pleural effusion (MPE) is a common condition, often associated with a 
high level of symptoms. In this review, several palliative treatments for 
symptomatic MPE are summarised, including repeated thoracentesis, pleurodesis 
and insertion of indwelling pleural catheters. Choice of treatment depends on 
patient symptoms, life expectancy, pleural fluid production, expected effect of 
oncological treatment, whether trapped lung is suspected or not, and patient 
preferences. Treatment should be discussed with a pulmonary specialist with 
knowledge of pleural diseases.

